column1: #Text=\* \*\*\[2024.1.7\]\*\* V2 data, reuslts and leaderboard are updated
#Text=üéâ üéâ üéâ   ## Leaderboard We present the results of voting using LLaVA-v1.5-13B as anchor.
#Text=The numbers denote \*win/tie/lose\* of a benchmarked model over LLaVA-v1.5-13B.
#Text=See more results of different evaluation protocols and anchors in our  \[paper\](https://arxiv.org/abs/2311.13951).
#Text=If this is not supported by your device, set `downcast\_bf16` to `false` and `mixed\_precision` to `fp16`
#Text=Explanations of parameters and outputs of the two methods are in \[workers/baseworker.py\](.
#Text=</details>  ### Self-Evaluation <details><summary>Click to expand</summary>  - Prepare the data in the format as shown in \[data/anchor.json\](.
#Text=/data/anchor.json), note that the key "unique\_idx", "gen\_model\_id", and "answer" are required.
#Text=- Put your OpenAI API key in \[evaluate.py\](.
#Text=/scripts/evaluate.py), please make sure you have access to model "gpt-4-vision-preview"
#Text=- Run `cd scripts & bash evaluate4elo.sh` for elo rating
#Text=- NOTE: The per sample criteria are not provided for self-evaluate and this self-evaluation process is just used for your reference.
#Text=If you wish your results to be displayed on the leaderboard, please refer to \[Submission for Leaderboard\](#submission-for-leaderboard).

#Text= ### Submission for Leaderboard Refer to instructions here. ## Citation ```angular2 @misc{ge2024mllmbench, title={MLLM-Bench: Evaluating Multimodal LLMs with Per-sample Criteria}, author={Wentao Ge and Shunian Chen and Guiming Hardy Chen and Zhihong Chen and Junying Chen and Shuo Yan and Chenghao Zhu and Ziyue Lin and Wenya Xie and Xinyi Zhang and Yichen Chai and Xiaoyu Liu and Nuo Chen and Dingjie Song and Xidong Wang and Anningzhe Gao and Zhiyi Zhang and Jianquan Li and Xiang Wan and Benyou Wang}, year={2024}, eprint={2311.13951}, archivePrefix={arXiv}, primaryClass={cs.CL} } ``` ## Star History
